race.comment: Big field with plenty of chances. CELLARMASTER (6) returned for his second campaign with a plugging fifth to Lancelot Du Lac over 1300m at Randwick Kensington. Winkers go on and maps to get the ideal run. MOVIE NIGHT (10) solid debut over the unsuitable trip when a respectable fourth over 1300m at Randwick Kensington. Should have come on strongly for this and will appreciate the good tempo. Each way. TINKLEJAZZ (13) big improver at her second career start when taking a sit and launching late for a narrow second in a 1250m Super Maiden at Canterbury. Can race a little closer and figure prominently. GREEN SPRING (3) has shown enough in three starts to date to give him a real show here and the chances don't end there.
